	<p>
		Tiia Kuokka, a master student in the International Business Communication program, is the first student to complete the AGI Challenge course. The course offers the students an opportunity to get involved, test and improve their skills while working with multi-disciplinary projects of Aalto Global Impact. The content of the course varies depending on the background and interests of each student, as well as on the current needs of Aalto Global Impact.<br><br>Kuokka participated in organizing the Weconomy Start kick-off event, which launched a program for Finnish companies interested in developing business in low-income markets in India and Sri Lanka. The Weconomy program is a joint project of Aalto Global Impact, World Vision, and Finpro. It offered Kuokka a good opportunity to learn about organizing events, collaborating with multiple parties and communication across organizations.<br><br>After completing the assignments, the students share their learning experience by writing a blog post in the <a target="_blank" title="" href="http://agichallenge.tumblr.com/">AGI Challenge blog</a>. In her post, Kuokka concludes that the course was a positive learn-by-doing experience: “I would recommend it to all Aalto business students who would like to get hands-on experience while working with multi-disciplinary projects.” Read more about the course <a target="_blank" title="" href="https://noppa.aalto.fi/noppa/kurssi/21e20000/esite">here</a>.<br class="Apple-interchange-newline">
